  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6820.84 sitting right on the max negative gamma strike (-43137.5M), dealers are aggressively buying the dip here as they're short gamma and need to hedge long delta exposure. The massive negative GEX wall cluster from 6800-6825 creates a high-volatility zone where any directional move will be amplified by dealer flow - breaks below 6800 or above 6840 (max positive gamma) should accelerate quickly. The 33.6% GEX surge indicates rapid options positioning changes, likely from the wall break event, making this a critical inflection point where dealer hedging will drive momentum rather than provide support.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect violent moves in either direction from current levels as dealers amplify any breakout.",
